lal. Damon Riccitiello is played by Max Mittelman @MaxMittelman . So, just who could Damon's secretary be...? #NMH3 www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2nPg42xsXg&t=5s\u00a0\u2026|last=SUDA51/\u9808\u7530\u525b\u4e00|date=2019-12-16|website=@suda_51|language=en|accessdate=2019-12-17}}</ref>\n|-\n\n|}\n\n===Live-action===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n|+ List of acting performances in film and television\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes !! Source\n|-\n| {{dts|2014|10|30|format=y}} || ''[[Two and a Half Men]]'' || Mechanical Demon (voice) || Ep. \"The Ol' Mexican Spinach\" || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MaxMittelman/status/527963510307708928|title=I'll be screaming my face off on tonight's season premiere of @TwoAndAHalfMen!!!|publisher=Twitter.com|accessdate=August 26, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{dts|2015|04|23|format=y}} || ''[[The Big Bang Theory (TV series)|The Big Bang Theory]]'' || Tech Support || Episode: \"The Gradulation Transmission\" || \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.maxmittelman.com/}}\n* {{ann|people|131942}}\n* {{IMDb name|5489754}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mittelman, Max}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:University of Southern California alumni]]\n[[Category:American male video game actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:People from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Max Mittelman\n| image = Max Mittelman.jpg\n| caption = Mittelman in 2017\n| birth_name = Maxwell Braden Mittelman\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1990|9|5}}\n| birth_place = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| alias = Jason Baker\n| occupation = Voice actor\n| years_active = 2013\u2013present\n| alma_mater = [[University of Southern California]]\n| credits = \n}}\n'''Maxwell Braden Mittelman''' (born September 5, 1990)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/search/record/results?count=20&englishSubcountryName=California&query=+givenname:Max~%20+surname:Mittleman~%20+birth_year:1990-2000~%20+record_country:%22United%20States%22%20+record_subcountry:%22United%20States,California%22|title=Maxwell Braden Mittelman|website=familysearch.org|access-date=2018-01-06}}</ref> is an American voice actor who provides voices for English versions of anime, animation and video games. Some of his major roles include [[List of One-Punch Man characters#Saitama|Saitama]] in ''[[One-Punch Man]]'', Kousei Arima in ''[[Your Lie in April]]'', [[List of The Seven Deadly Sins characters#King|King]] from ''[[The Seven Deadly Sins (manga)|The Seven Deadly Sins]]'', Ritsu Kageyama in ''[[Mob Psycho 100]]'', Inaho Kaizuka in ''[[Aldnoah.Zero]]'', [[Atsushi Nakajima (Bungo Stray Dogs)|Atsushi Nakajima]] in ''[[Bungo Stray Dogs]]'' and Io Flemming in ''[[Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt]]''. In video games, he voices Ryuji Sakamoto in ''[[Persona 5]]'' and Troy Calypso in ''[[Borderlands 3]]''.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Anime===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n|+ List of dubbing performances in anime\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes !! Source\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2014 || ''[[Toradora!]]'' || [[Toradora!#Supporting characters|Hisamitsu Noto]] || 22 episodes || <ref name=\"Sacanime\"/>\n|-\n| ''[[List of Magi: The Labyrinth of Magic episodes|Magi: The Labyrinth of Magic]]'' || [[List of Magi: The Labyrinth of Magic characters#Other characters|Yunan]] || Ep. 25 ||\n|-\n| ''[[Doraemon (2005 anime)|Doraemon]]'' || [[List of Doraemon characters#Nobi family|Soby]] || Also ''[[Stand by Me Doraemon]]'' || <ref name=\"Sacanime\"/>\n|-\n| ''[[Naruto shippuden|Naruto Shippuden]]'' || Young Hashirama Senju || 3 episodes ||\n|-\n| ''[[Blood Lad]]'' || [[Blood Lad#East Demon World|Yoshida the Mimic]] || 6 episodes || <ref name=\"Sacanime\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-05-16/viz-media-announce