en]]'' || Mechanical Demon (voice) || Ep. \"The Ol' Mexican Spinach\" || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MaxMittelman/status/527963510307708928|title=I'll be screaming my face off on tonight's season premiere of @TwoAndAHalfMen!!!|publisher=Twitter.com|accessdate=August 26, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{dts|2015|04|23|format=y}} || ''[[The Big Bang Theory (TV series)|The Big Bang Theory]]'' || Tech Support || Episode: \"The Gradulation Transmission\" || \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.maxmittelman.com/}}\n* {{ann|people|131942}}\n* {{IMDb name|5489754}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mittelman, Max}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:University of Southern California alumni]]\n[[Category:American male video game actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:People from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n", "name_user": "Quebec99", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed reference", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Max_Mittelman"}
{"title_page": "F\u00e1bio Gurgel", "text_new": "{{short description|Brazilian martial artist}}\n{{Infobox martial artist\n| name            = Fabio Gurgel\n| other_names     = \"The General\"\n| image           =\n| alt             =\n| caption         =\n| birth_name      =\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1970|1|18}}\n| birth_place     = \n| death_date      = \n| death_place     =\n| death_cause     =\n| residence       = [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]\n| nationality     = {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Brazilians|Brazilian]]\n| height          = {{height|ft=6|in=1}}\n| weight          = {{convert|205|lb|kg st|abbr=on}}\n| weight_class    = \n| reach           = \n| style           = [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]]\n| stance          = \n| fighting_out_of = \n| team            = [[Alliance Jiu Jitsu]]\n| rank            = {{color box|black}} ''6th degree black belt in [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]]''<ref>[http://www.fabiogurgel.com.br/english/fabio-gurgel.php Fabio Gurgel Biography]. URL accessed on September 30, 2010.</ref>\n| teacher         = [[Romero Cavalcanti|Romero \"Jacare\" Cavalcanti]]\n| students        = [[Demian Maia]]<br />[[Marcelo Garcia (grappler)|Marcelo Garcia]]\n| years_active    = 1991-1997 (MMA)\n| mma_win         = 3\n| mma_kowin       = \n| mma_subwin      = 3\n| mma_decwin      = \n| mma_loss        = 2\n| mma_koloss      = \n| mma_subloss     = \n| mma_decloss     = \n| mma_draw        = \n| mma_nc          =\n| url             = {{URL|www.fabiogurgel.com.br}}\n| sherdog         = 146\n| footnotes       =\n| updated         =\n}}\n\n{{MedalTableTop}}\n{{MedalCountry | {{BRA}} }}\n{{MedalSport  | [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[World Jiu-Jitsu Championship|World Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold | 1996 [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]] | -94kg}}\n{{MedalGold | 1997 [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]] | -94kg}}\n{{MedalGold | 2000 [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]] | -94kg}}\n{{MedalGold | 2001 [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]] | -94kg}}\n{{MedalSport  | [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[European Championship (Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu)|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold | 2010 [[Lisbon, Portugal]] | -94kg}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Brazilian Nationals Championship (Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu)|Brazilian National Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold | 1996 [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]] | -94 kg}}\n{{MedalBottom}}\n'''F\u00e1bio Duca Gurgel do Amaral''' (born January 18, 1970 in [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]) is a 4-time   [[World Jiu-Jitsu Championship|World Jiu-Jitsu Champion]] (1996-2001).<ref>Gurgel, F (2007): Brazilian Jiu Jitsu Advanced Techniques: front cover</ref> He has been practicing [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]] (BJJ) since the age of 13 and received his [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu ranking system|black belt]] at the age of 19 from [[Romero Cavalcanti|Romero \"Jacar\u00e9\" Cavalcanti]].<ref>Gurgel, F (2007): Brazilian Jiu Jitsu Basic Techniques: p. 151</ref> Along with Cavalcanti he is co-founder of the [[Alliance Jiu Jitsu]] Team.<ref>Gracie Mag [http://www.graciemag.com/2012/05/brazilian-bjj-nationals-nivaldo-oliveiras-star-shines-brightest/ Brazilian BJJ Nationals] 2012 \"In the stands F\u00e1bio Gurgel, L\u00e9o Vieira, Ramon Lemos, Rodrigo Cavaca and Andr\u00e9 Marola represented some of the traditional powerhouse teams that were in the running.\"</ref>\n\nHe is the teacher of BJJ and ADCC World Champion [[Marcelo Garcia (grappler)|Marcelo Garcia]].<ref>Garcia, M (2008): X-guard: For Brazilian Jiu-jitsu, No Gi Grappling, and Mixed Martial Arts</ref> Gurgel is President of the Professional League of Jiu-Jitsu.<ref>Gurgel, F (2007): Brazilian Jiu Jitsu Advanced Techniques: page 140</ref>\n\n==Brazilian Jiu Jitsu==\nAwards and achievements:\n*1986 - Awarded purple belt\n*1988 - Awarded brown belt\n*1989 - Awarded black belt\n*1993 - Founded Alliance\n*1994 - Brazilian National Champion\n*1995 - Brazilian National Champion\n*1996 - Brazilian National Champion, World Champion\n*1997 - World Champion\n*1999 - Brazilian National Champion\n*2000 - World Champion\n*2001 - World Champion\n*2007 - European Champion\n*2008 - Awarded 5th Degree black belt by CBJJ, Pan-Am Champion\n*2009 - European Champion\n*2010 - European Champion\n*2013 - Awarded 6th Degree black belt\n\n== Instructor Lineage ==\n[[Mitsuyo Maeda|Mitsuyo \"Count Koma\" Maeda]] \u2192 [[Carlos Gracie|Carlos Gracie, Sr.]] \u2192 [[Helio Gracie]] \u2192 [[Rolls Gracie]] \u2192 [[Romero \"Jacare\" Cavalcanti]] \u2192 Fabio Gurgel\n\n==Books==\n*Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu Advanced Techniques (2007)\n*Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu Basic Techniques (2007)\n\n==Mixed martial arts record==\n{{MMArecordbox\n|wins=3\n|losses=2\n|ko-wins=0\n|ko-losses=0\n|sub-wins=3\n|sub-losses=0\n|dec-wins=0\n|dec-losses=2\n}}\n{{MMA record start}}\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|3\u20132\n|[[Mark Kerr (fighter)|Mark Kerr]]\n|Decision (Unanimous)\n|rowspan=3|World Vale Tudo Championship 3\n|rowspan=3|January 19, 1997\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|30:00\n|rowspan=3|[[Brazil]]\n|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|align=center|3\u20131\n|Michael Pacholik\n|Submission (Punches)\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|4:50\n|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|align=center|2\u20131\n|[[Patrick Smith (fighter)|Patrick Smith]]\n|TKO (Retirement due to Fan Interference)\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|0:50\n|\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|1\u20131\n|[[Jerry Bohlander]]\n|Decision (Unanimous)\n|[[UFC 11]]\n|September 20, 1996\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|15:00\n|[[Augusta, Georgia]]\n|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|align=center|1\u20130\n|Denilson Maia\n|Submission (Punches)\n|Desafio: Jiu-Jitsu vs. Luta Livre\n|September 26, 1991\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|9:55\n|[[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]]\n|\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu practitioners]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090802112044/http://www.fabiogurgel.com.br/english/index.php Fabio Gurgel]\n*[http://www.alliancebjj.com Alliance Jiu Jitsu]\n*[http://www.bjjheroes.com/bjj-fighters/fabio-gurgel-wiki Fabio Gurgel BJJ Heroes]\n* {{Sherdog}}\n* {{UFC|F\u00e1bio-Gurgel}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gurgel, Fabio}}\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Rio de Janeiro (city)]]\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Brazilian male writers]]\n[[Category:Brazilian practitioners of Brazilian jiu-jitsu]]\n[[Category:Brazilian submission wrestlers]]\n[[Category:Brazilian male mixed martial artists]]\n[[Category:People awarded a black belt in Brazilian jiu-jitsu]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Brazilian martial artist}}\n{{Infobox martial artist\n| name            = Fabio Gurgel\n| other_names     = \"The General\"\n| image           =\n| alt             =\n| caption         =\n| birth_name      =\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1970|1|18}}\n| birth_place     = \n| death_date      = \n| death_place     =\n| death_cause     =\n| residence       = [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]\n| nationality     = {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Brazilians|Brazilian]]\n| height          = {{height|ft=6|in=1}}\n| weight          = {{convert|205|lb|kg st|abbr=on}}\n| weight_class    = \n| reach           = \n| style           = [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]]\n| stance          = \n| fighting_out_of = \n| team            = [[Alliance Jiu Jitsu]]\n| rank            = {{color box|black}} ''6th degree black belt in [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]]''<ref>[http://www.fabiogurgel.com.br/english/fabio-gurgel.php Fabio Gurgel Biography]. URL accessed on September 30, 2010.</ref>\n| teacher         = [[Romero Cavalcanti|Romero \"Jacare\" Cavalcanti]]\n| students        = [[Demian Maia]]<br />[[Marcelo Garcia (grappler)|Marcelo Garcia]]\n| years_active    = 1991-1997 (MMA)\n| mma_win         = 3\n| mma_kowin       = \n| mma_subwin      = 3\n| mma_decwin      = \n| mma_loss        = 2\n| mma_koloss      = \n| mma_subloss     = \n| mma_decloss     = \n| mma_draw        = \n| mma_nc          =\n| url             = {{URL|www.fabiogurgel.com.br}}\n| sherdog         = 146\n| footnotes       =\n| updated         =\n}}\n\n{{MedalTableTop}}\n{{MedalCountry | {{BRA}} }}\n{{MedalSport  | [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[World Jiu-Jitsu Championship|World Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold | 1996 [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]] | -94kg}}\n{{MedalGold | 1997 [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]] | -94kg}}\n{{MedalGold | 2000 [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]] | -94kg}}\n{{MedalGold | 2001 [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]] | -94kg}}\n{{MedalSport  | [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[European Championship (Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu)|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold | 2010 [[Lisbon, Portugal]] | -94kg}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Brazilian Nationals Championship (Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu)|Brazilian National Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold | 1996 [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]] | -94 kg}}\n{{MedalBottom}}\n'''F\u00e1bio Duca Gurgel do Amaral''' (born January 18, 1970 in [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]) is a 4-time   [[World Jiu-Jitsu Championship|World Jiu-Jitsu Champion]] (1996-2001).<ref>Gurgel, F (2007): Brazilian Jiu Jitsu Advanced Techniques: front cover</ref> He has been practicing [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]] (BJJ) since the age of 13 and received his [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu ranking system|black belt]] at the age of 19 from [[Romero Cavalcanti|Romero \"Jacar\u00e9\" Cavalcanti]].<ref>Gurgel, F (2007): Brazilian Jiu Jitsu Basic Techniques: p. 151</ref> Along with Cavalcanti he is co-founder of the [[Alliance Jiu Jitsu]] Team.<ref>Gracie Mag [http://www.graciemag.com/2012/05/brazilian-bjj-nationals-nivaldo-oliveiras-star-shines-brightest/ Brazilian BJJ Nationals] 2012 \"In the stands F\u00e1bio Gurgel, L\u00e9o Vieira, Ramon Lemos, Rodrigo Cavaca and Andr\u00e9 Marola represented some of the traditional powerhouse teams that were in the running.\"</ref>\n\nHe is the teacher of BJJ and ADCC World Champion [[Marcelo Garcia (grappler)|Marcelo Garcia]].<ref>Garcia, M (2008): X-guard: For Brazilian Jiu-jitsu, No Gi Grappling, and Mixed Martial Arts</ref> Gurgel is President of the Professional League of Jiu-Jitsu.<ref>Gurgel, F (2007): Brazilian Jiu Jitsu Advanced Techniques: page 140</ref>\n\n==Brazilian Jiu Jitsu==\nAwards and achievements:\n*1986 - Awarded purple belt\n*1988 - Awarded brown belt\n*1989 - Awarded black belt\n*1993 - Founded Alliance\n*1994 - Brazilian National Champion\n*1995 - Brazilian National Champion\n*1996 - Brazilian National Champion, World Champion\n*1997 - World Champion\n*1999 - Brazilian National Champion\n*2000 - World Champion\n*2001 - World Champion\n*2007 - European Champion\n*2008 - Awarded 5th Degree black belt by CBJJ, Pan-Am Champion\n*2009 - European Champion\n*2010 - European Champion\n*2013 - Awarded 6th Degree black belt\n\n== Instructor Lineage ==\n[[Mitsuyo Maeda|Mitsuyo \"Count Koma\" Maeda]] \u2192 [[Carlos Gracie|Carlos Gracie, Sr.]] \u2192 [[Helio Gracie]] \u2192 [[Rolls Gracie]] \u2192 [[Romero \"Jacare\" Cavalcanti]] \u2192 Fabio Gurgel\n\n==Books==\n*Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu Advanced Techniques (2007)\n*Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu Basic Techniques (2007)\n\n==Mixed martial arts record==\n{{MMArecordbox\n|wins=3\n|losses=2\n|ko-wins=0\n|ko-losses=0\n|sub-wins=3\n|sub-losses=0\n|dec-wins=0\n|dec-losses=2\n}}\n{{MMA record start}}\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|3\u20132\n|[[Mark Kerr (fighter)|Mark Kerr]]\n|Decision (Unanimous)\n|rowspan=3|World Vale Tudo Championship 3\n|rowspan=3|January 19, 1997\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|30:00\n|rowspan=3|[[Brazil]]\n|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|align=center|3\u20131\n|Michael Pacholik\n|Submission (Punches)\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|4:50\n|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|align=center|2\u20131\n|[[Patrick Smith (fighter)|Patrick Smith]]\n|TKO (Retirement due to Fan Interference)\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|0:50\n|\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|1\u20131\n|[[Jerry Bohlander]]\n|Decision (Unanimous)\n|[[UFC 11]]\n|September 20, 1996\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|15:00\n|[[Augusta, Georgia]]\n|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|align=center|1\u20130\n|Denilson Maia\n|Submission (Pun